<subSubSection pageNumber="559" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="559">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="559">Note:</emphasis>
See review by Reveal &amp; Barrie (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="559">Phytologia</emphasis>
71: 456-461. 1991), who conclude that the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
belongs to what has been known as 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Pers." authorityName="Pers." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lespedeza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="559">L. violacea</emphasis>
(L.) Pers.
</taxonomicName>
, and that the type of the latter is a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton" authorityName="Britton" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lespedeza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="559">L. intermedia</emphasis>
Britton
</taxonomicName>
. Turland &amp; Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="559">Taxon</emphasis>
46: 471. 1997) were therefore wrong to indicate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Hedysarum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="559">H. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lespedeza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="559">L. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Akiyamaâ€™s">Akiyama's</normalizedToken>
type choice there is pre-dated by that of Britton, albeit using the same element.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
